rfcmarkup (1.101)

  * Fixed two issues with quoting, reported and analysed by Roman Donchenko
    <dpb@corrigendum.ru>: Missing quoting of double-quotes in DC meta-
    information, and overquoting in reference link title attributes.

  * Fixed an issue found because of an issue report from Leif Halvard
    Silli <malform@malform.no>,  where Latin-1 content was delivered
    as utf-8, without re-coding.  This affected the rendering of RFC 2557.

 -- Henrik Levkowetz <henrik@levkowetz.com>  01 May 2012 16:41:19 +0200

rfcmarkup (1.100)

  * Added stripping of whitespace and formfeeds at the end of documents,
    to avoid blank trailing pages, after bugreport and analysis from
    Martin J. Duerst <duerst@it.aoyama.ac.jp>

 -- Henrik Levkowetz <henrik@levkowetz.com>  13 Mar 2012 12:20:35 +0100

rfcmarkup (1.99)

  * Applied a patch from julian.reschke@gmx.de to make section title
    numbers into links to self, for ease of emailing links into documents.

  * Added a link to the xml source file in the top menu, where such exists.

  * In order to support correct sibling links when the html is used to
    produce pdfs, the 'staticpath' argument was changes so as to accept
    a path argument instead of just a boolean.  If the argument is 'true'
    the path is set to '.' (legacy support).

  * In order to support correct page breaking when the html is used to
    produce pdfs, page breaks are now also indicated by '<!--NewPage-->'.

 -- Henrik Levkowetz <henrik@levkowetz.com>  27 Nov 2011 17:08:43 +0200

