rfcmarkup (1.64)

  * The special handling of RFC 2606 domains (.example, example.com, etc.)
    used too greedy regexes, and could obliterate non-link text.  Fixed.
    Thanks to Jim Bell for discovering this problem.

  * Added some limitation on URLs broken across lines: the ':' character
    (used for instance between domain and port number) is now only recognized
    on the first line of the URL, in order to handle consecutive lines of
    URLs better.

